The freestream is the air far upstream of an aerodynamic body, that is, before the body has a chance to deflect, slow down or compress the air. Freestream conditions are usually denoted with a 
  
    
      
        ∞
      
    
    {\displaystyle \infty }
   symbol, e.g. 
  
    
      
        
          V
          
            ∞
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle V_{\infty }}
  , meaning the freestream velocity
